{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01AECXRdJciGmiagujzwyGC6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→MODULE: src/services\n     2→FILES: 30\n     3→RESPONSIBILITY: Core service layer — AI CLI execution, session management, messaging, pipeline control, monitoring\n     4→INTERFACES:\n     5→- executeAiCli(options): Promise<AiCliExecutionResult> — unified AI CLI executor with process tracking\n     6→- interruptAiCli(sessionId): {ok, pid?, error?} — interrupt running AI task\n     7→- createMessageRouter({aiCliExecutor, sessionStore, realtimeHub}): MessageRouter — F-018 unified message processor\n     8→- processMessage({channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId?, hooks?}): Promise<{reply}> — route message through AI CLI\n     9→- createSessionBindService({bindingsPath}): SessionBindingService — F-018 factory with deferred init\n    10→- SessionBindingService.bindSession(webId, chatId): {ok} — bind web session to Telegram chat\n    11→- SessionBindingService.getBoundChatId(webId): string|null — lookup binding\n    12→- SessionBindingService.getBoundWebSessions(chatId): string[] — reverse lookup\n    13→- SessionBindingService.ensureReady(): Promise<void> — wait for deferred init\n    14→- sessionStore.append(key, role, content) — append message to session\n    15→- sessionStore.toPrompt(key, channel): string — build prompt with context\n    16→- realtimeHub.subscribe(key, listener): unsubscribe — SSE event pub/sub\n    17→- realtimeHub.publish(key, event) — broadcast event to subscribers\n    18→- chatWithSession({channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks}): Promise<reply> — legacy Web chat (deprecated by F-018)\n    19→DEPENDENCIES:\n    20→- uses: node:child_process: spawn for AI CLI process\n    21→- uses: zod: config validation\n    22→- uses: node:fs/promises: session persistence, bindings file\n    23→- imports: src/config.js: runtime configuration\n    24→- imports: src/security/guard.js: sanitizeInput\n    25→KEY_FILES:\n    26→- ai-cli-service.js: AI CLI executor with heartbeat, timeout, metrics (564 lines)\n    27→- message-router.js: F-018 unified message processor (128 lines)\n    28→- session-bind.js: F-018 session binding with persistence (~220 lines)\n    29→- session-store.js: in-memory session state (427 lines)\n    30→- realtime-hub.js: SSE event pub/sub (35 lines)\n    31→- chat-service.js: legacy chat via codebuddy adapter (80 lines, deprecated)\n    32→TRAPS:\n    33→- SessionBindingService uses deferred init — always call ensureReady() before sync methods in async contexts\n    34→- SessionBindingService persistence is fire-and-forget — tests must call flush() to verify file writes\n    35→- messageRouter does not expose heartbeat hooks — Telegram heartbeat progress disabled after F-018 migration\n    36→- Runtime bindings created via POST /api/bind do NOT auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push (F-018 gap)\n    37→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e46239e5-8540-42b3-8b45-910022f21a71","uuid":"f3a2155d-e610-4e47-9fde-67bd7ee54ac9","timestamp":"2026-03-22T10:51:13.796Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/services.prizm","content":"MODULE: src/services\nFILES: 30\nRESPONSIBILITY: Core service layer — AI CLI execution, session management, messaging, pipeline control, monitoring\nINTERFACES:\n- executeAiCli(options): Promise<AiCliExecutionResult> — unified AI CLI executor with process tracking\n- interruptAiCli(sessionId): {ok, pid?, error?} — interrupt running AI task\n- createMessageRouter({aiCliExecutor